node.statement: Step 1.2.3 (Non-melonic suppression â€” q-tetrahedron): The first non-melonic correction involves the quantum 6j symbol {j j j; j j j}_q. Its large-j asymptotics are controlled by the quantum Racah formula. For generic q > 0 (not a root of unity), the quantum 6j symbol has the same 1/sqrt(j) suppression as the classical case, giving a 1/sqrt(j) suppression of the tetrahedron diagram.
